        <p>You will now play 2048 for a short amount of time. First read these instructions before continuing to the next page.</p>
        <p><strong>How to play: </strong></p>
        <ul>

          <li>2048 is a matching game where your job is to combine matching tiles to create larger numbered tiles. </li>
          <li>When there are no more moves left, and the board is full, the game is over.</li>
          <li>If you want to get to the mythical 2048 tile, you'll have to think strategically and plan your moves carefully.</li>
          <li>Random number blocks will appear on your board and you can move them using the arrow buttons on your keyboard.</li>
          <li>Combining two equal tiles will create a new block equaling the sum of the two previous blocks.</li>
          <li>The game ends when you reach 2048 or your board becomes completely full.</li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>Keep playing: </strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Your scores will be recorded.
          <li>If you play more than one game, your goal is to improve your score as you go.
          <li>Play the game until the page automatically redirects to the next part of the experiment.
        </ul>
